<HEADLINE> McRae Backs to Top World Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 6 (Xinhua) -- Colin McRae of Britain put up his form
and won in the Corsica rally to take the world championship lead
on Wednesday in Corsica.
</P>
<P>
The Scot, driving a Subaru, finished 27.2 seconds ahead of
Francois Delecour of France, in a Peugeot 306, to overtake
Spaniard Carlos Sainz for the leader place in the world standings.
</P>
<P>
Sainz, the Monte Carlo winner, was only eighth in his Toyota
about four minutes behind, and is now two points behind McRae in
second place.
</P>
<P>
McRae's Subaru team mate Piero Liatti of Italy took the third
place.
</P>
<P>
Defending world champion Tommi Makinen of Finland is now sixth
with 10 points trailing the leader. 
</P>
</TEXT>
