<HEADLINE> 12 Vietnamese Fishermen Killed in Whirlwind </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, May 6 (Xinhua) -- 12 Vietnamese fishermen were killed
and about 30 others reported missing in high seas after a
whirlwind blowing at up to 100 kph hit the country's central coast
off Quang Ngai province, the Vietnam news agency reported
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The twister, which struck on Monday morning, also sank three
fishing trawlers and damaged three others.
</P>
<P>
Five fishing boats carrying about eight fishermen each are
among the missing.
</P>
<P>
The whirlwind also sank 14 boats and caused 15 other boats to
go missing off the coast of the neighboring province Quang Nam.
</P>
<P>
On Sunday, two people were struck dead by lightning during a
thunderstorm in the central province of Quang Tri. 
</P>
</TEXT>
