<HEADLINE> Vietnam, Japan Boost Cooperation in Coal Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, May 6 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam and Japan will jointly carry
out technological research for coal exploitation at Duong Huy coal
mine in Vietnam's biggest coal mining province of Quang Ninh,
according to Vietnamese press reports.
</P>
<P>
The two-year project will start within the year according to a
memorandum of understanding which has been just signed by the
Vietnam Coal Corporation (VINACOAL) and the Japanese Coal
Corporation (JCOAL).
</P>
<P>
About 40 percent of Vietnam's exported coal is shipped to
Japan, which wants to ensure a stable source of coal from Vietnam,
according to an official of the Japanese Ministry of Industry and
Trade.
</P>
<P>
Negotiations on a five-year project to conduct coal exploration
at the Red River Delta and a two-year project to exchange
technicians are underway between Vietnam and Japan.
</P>
<P>
Furthermore, VINACOAL and its Japanese partners will probably
implement projects to study ventilation in coal mines, to build a
safety control center, and to build a coal sorting factory at Cua
Ong mine, also in Quang Ninh province, said the report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
