<HEADLINE> About Ten Heads of State Confirm Attendance to  WTO Ministerial Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, May 6 (Xinhua) -- Up to now about ten heads of state or
government have confirmed their participation in the 50th
anniversary of the multilateral trading system to be held on May
19 here in Geneva, the World Trade Organization (WTO) announced
here monday.
</P>
<P>
Those having confirmed their attendance are Brazilian President
Fernando Henrique Cardoso, Canadian Prime Minister Jean Chretien,
European Commission President Jacques Santer, Italian Prime
Minister Romano Prodi, Norwegian Prime Minister Kjell Majne
Bondevik, Singaporian Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong, Slovenian
Prime Minister Janez Drnovsek, Swiss President Flavio Cotti, and
British Prime Minister Tony Blair.
</P>
<P>
WTO sources said that U.S. President Bill Clinton would like to
attend the celebrations but they could not confirm his attendance
at the moment.
</P>
<P>
They said that 10 others, many of them from the African
continent, were expected to come to Geneva for the event. 
</P>
