<DOCNO> XIE19980507.0015 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sinn Fein to Vote in Favor of N.Irish Peace Deal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 6 (Xinhua) -- Sinn Fein, the political wing of IRA,
will recommend a "yes" vote in a referendum on the Northern
Ireland peace agreement, BBC radio reported on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
It reported that a document released to reporters in Belfast
said Sinn Fein's policy-directing national executive had
recommended that members should campaign for it in referendums on
both Northern Ireland and the Irish Republic on May 22.
</P>
<P>
"The (national executive), in the context of our legitimate
reservation, calls for a yes vote in the referendums north and
south," the document said.
</P>
<P>
The referendums will be held on the peace agreement struck on
April 10 by the major political parties in the province, including
Sinn Fein.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Irish Republican Army was reported to have
changed its rules to allow members of Sinn Fein to take seats in a
proposed power-sharing assembly in Belfast.
</P>
<P>
In a major change in favor of the peace process in Northern
Ireland, IRA had dropped a constitutional bar to Sinn Fein members
sitting in what the outlawed guerrilla group calls "subservient"
parliaments.
</P>
<P>
Sinn Fein and the IRA had been opposed to the participation in
an assembly before, saying to do so would legitimize British
jurisdiction over Northern Ireland. 
</P>
</TEXT>
