<HEADLINE> UK Must Be Prepared for Single Currency: Beckett </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 6 (Xinhua) - Businesses in Britain will only thrive
if they plan ahead for the euro, the President of the Board of
Trade, Margaret Beckett told audience at a seminar in Birmingham
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
This is the first in a series of events to be held around the
country to discuss how business should prepare for the single
currency.
</P>
<P>
Beckett said: "The introduction of the single currency - the
euro - across the European Union on 1 January next year will
change the business environment not just in those 11 countries,
bet across the whole of Europe."
</P>
<P>
Many KU companies believe that because Britain is not joining
in the first wave, they do not need to take any action, Beckett
warned: "They are wrong." Adding "The euro zone will account for
nearly half of British exports and over 40% OF British overseas
direct investment."
</P>
<P>
So even though Britain is not in the first wave, its businesses
will be affected and must be prepared to address the changes which
EMU will bring, she stressed. 
