<HEADLINE> Ethiopia's Regional Association Calls for Public </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, May 6 (Xinhua) -- The Oromia Development
Association of Ethiopia has called on the public to support its
effort in constructing schools for about four million children so
far deprived access to education.
</P>
<P>
The association made the call in its general assembly which
began on Tuesday at Nazeret, some 90 kilometers southeast of
Addis Ababa, the Ethiopian News Agency reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Oromia region in the south of the country is the largest
region in Ethiopia, with a population of about 20 million.
</P>
<P>
The participation of the public as well as governmental and
non-governmental organizations is imperative to expand
educational facilities, the cornerstones in the fight against
backwardness, said the association.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that 159 of the 1,000 children in the region
die before their fifth birthday.
</P>
<P>
The association has plans to raise educational and health
coverage to 50 percent against the present 31 and 42 percent
respectively in the next five years.  
</P>
