<DOCNO> XIE19980507.0050 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-06 19:54 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 27th Arab Financial Conference Opens in Beirut </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, May 6 (Xinhua) -- The 27th session of Arab Financial
Institution Conference opened here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-five Arab finance or economy ministers, 14 governors of
central bank and more than 300 bankers and economists from Arab
countries and international institutions attended the two-day
meeting.
</P>
<P>
In his opening speech, Lebanese Prime Minister Rafik Hariri
called on the Arab countries to bolster cooperation in every
domain, especial in finance and economy.
</P>
<P>
He spoke highly of the achievements Lebanon has gained after
the 15-year-long civil war ended in 1990.
</P>
<P>
The convening of the conference indicated that Lebanon has
restored its financial and economic role in the region, Hariri
said.
</P>
<P>
The last time that Lebanon hosted the conference was in 1973,
two years before the country plunged into the civil war, which
destroyed its position as a regional financial center.
</P>
<P>
The ongoing conference will focus on the challenges that Arab
financial sector will face in the next century, economic reforms
in the Arab countries, lessons from the Asian financial crisis and
its impact on Arab economies.
</P>
<P>
It will also discuss the operations of Arab stock and bonds
markets and investment opportunities in Egypt and Lebanon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
