<HEADLINE> China Donates Training Implements to Tanzania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, May 6 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government has
donated implements worth three million Yuan (about 36,200 U.S.
Dollars) to Tanzania for the training of students at technical
schools.
</P>
<P>
The implements were handed over by the Chinese ambassador to
Tanzania, Zhang Hongxi, to the Minister of Labor and Youth
Development Sabastian Kinyondo Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The implements, including 600 sewing machines, a batch of
carpentry, bench work, bricklaying and pipe fitting tools, have
been granted in accordance with an agreement between the Chinese
and Tanzanian governments in September of 1996.
</P>
<P>
At the signing ceremony for the hand-over, the minister said
that the implements is of great significance to creating
self-employment opportunities in Tanzania, which has an
unemployed population of up to four million, most of whom are
young men. 
</P>
</TEXT>
