<HEADLINE> Chinese, Kazakhstan Prime Ministers Hold Talks (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji said
today that China is ready to make joint efforts with Kazakhstan to
develop a bilateral relationship of comprehensive cooperation
toward the next century.
</P>
<P>
During 100-minute talks with visiting Prime Minister Nurlan
Balgimbaev of Kazakhstan here this afternoon, Zhu said that the
visit would have positive impact on the growth of Sino-Kazakhstan
good-neighborly ties.
</P>
<P>
He said that Sino-Kazakhstan exchange and cooperation in
various areas have constantly expanded and made satisfying
achievements featured by increasingly stable bilateral political
relationship of mutual trust since the two countries established
diplomatic ties six years ago.
</P>
<P>
The joint statement and a series of agreements concerning
border issues and arms control signed by China and Kazakhstan have
laid a solid political and legal foundation for the development of
bilateral relations, Zhu added.
</P>
<P>
Zhu emphasized that China has always placed importance to its
friendly ties with Kazakhstan and there exist no obstacles for the
two neighboring countries to foster a relationship on the basis of
equality and mutual benefit.
</P>
<P>
Balgimbaev agreed with Zhu on his evaluation of bilateral
relations. Kazakhstan is satisfied with the smooth growth of the
two countries' ties and hopes that leaders of the two nations
would increase mutual contact and exchange visits to help
strengthen bilateral cooperative relations, he told Zhu.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980507.0090 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese, Kazakhstan Prime Ministers Hold Talks (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Balgimbaev told Zhu that Kazakhstan would continue to firmly
adhere to the "one China" policy and would never allow any
national splittists to carry out activities within its territory.
</P>
<P>
Zhu expressed his thanks for Kazakhstan's stance of supporting
China on the issue of opposing national splittists.
</P>
<P>
On bilateral economic and trade cooperation, Balgimbaev said
such cooperation has been effective and Kazakhstan welcomes
Chinese enterprises to invest or do business in the country.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said that trade volume between China and Kazakhstan has
registered fairly fast increase in recent years thanks to the
joint efforts of both sides. The Chinese government encourages
cooperation between enterprises of the two countries, especially
supports large firms of the two countries to conduct direct
exchange and implement the agreements which are already reached,
Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
The two prime ministers also exchanged views on certain
projects of economic and trade cooperation. They agreed that the
economic and trade ties between the two countries would have a
broad prospect since they enjoy geographic advantages.
</P>
<P>
Following the talks, Zhu and Balgimbaev attended a signing
ceremony for five agreements, including those on China's gratis
aid to Kazakhstan and bilateral cooperation in the fields of
space, tourism, sports and culture.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the talks, Zhu presided over a welcoming ceremony in
honor of Balgimbaev, who is also scheduled to tour east China's
Jiangsu Province, Shanghai Municipality and northwest China's
Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
Balgimbaev and his party arrived here earlier this afternoon
for an official visit to China at Zhu's invitation.
</P>
<P>
This is Balgimbaev's first China trip since he became prime
minister last year. 
</P>
