<HEADLINE> Burley Named Scottish Footballer of the Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Celtic midfielder Craig Burley was
named as the Scottish Football Writers' player of the year in
Glasgow on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
He polled 68 percent of the votes to become the first Celtic
player to win the award since Paul McStay in 1988.
</P>
<P>
Since transfering to Glasgow from Chelsea at the end of last
season, Burley has helped take Celtic to the brink of their first
Scottish player to win the award since Paul McStay in 1988.
</P>
<P>
Burley's team mates Jackie McNamara, last month voted the
players' Player of the Year, goalkeeper Jonathan Gould and Swede
Henrik Larsson were second, third and fourth respectively.
</P>
</TEXT>
