<BODY>
<HEADLINE>   Vietnam Parliament Confirms Central Bank Governor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's National Assembly
(parliament) Thursday approved Permanent Deputy Prime Minister
Nguyen Tan Dung as the new governor of the State Bank of Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
Dung was nominated for the post by Prime Minister Phan Van Khai.
</P>
<P>
The post has been vacant since last October and a deputy
governor has been serving as acting governor.
</P>
<P>
Dung, 49, is the youngest in Vietnam's top leadership. He was
elected a member of the Political Bureau of the ruling Communist
Party at its Eighth National Congress in July 1996.
</P>
<P>
He became permanent deputy prime minister in last September.
</P>
<P>
Dung said in his government report delivered to the National
Assembly last month that the impact of the financial crisis in
Southeast Asia and the distablizing factors in Vietnam's
macroeconomic environment make it necessary to reform the
country's financial and monetary system. 
</P>
</TEXT>
