<HEADLINE> Nanning Trade Fair Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, May 7 (Xinhua) -- The `98 Nanning Trade Fair opened
here today, with contracts for orders worth 100 million US dollars
signed on the first day.
</P>
<P>
A total of 13 contracts were signed, of which six involve
foreign-funded projects.
</P>
<P>
The biggest transaction was a project to be co-constructed by
the Bien Company of the US and the Nanning Economic and
Technological Development Company. It will cost an estimated 87
million US dollars. Upon completion, it will become a leading
trade center for both China and the world as a whole for articles
for students' use.
</P>
<P>
N. Thoke, president of Bien, said, "We have a special interest
and full confidence in investment in Nanning as it is adjacent to
the Beibu Gulf and Southeast Asia, and the Chinese government has
shifted its emphasis of investment to the central and western
parts of China and ethnic-minority areas in recent years."
</P>
<P>
More than 500 businessmen, including some from the United
States, Canada, Japan, Singapore and Malaysia, attended today's
opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Nanning, the political, economic and cultural center of south
China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, has approved the
establishment of 645 firms funded by 23 countries and regions
since it opened to the outside world in 1991. The city attracted
271 million US dollars in foreign investment last year, up 13.58
percent over the same period of last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
