<HEADLINE> Merit Cup Jumps To Lead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Merit Cup beat Toshiba to steal the
lead of the Whitbread Round the World Race after the eighth leg on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Merit Cup, skipped by Grant Dalton, built up a gap of more than
six nautical miles after overnight sailing with Dennis Conner's
Toshiba trailing at second.
</P>
<P>
Former leader Innovation Kvaerner dropped back to third place,
more than 17 miles adrift of the leader.
</P>
<P>
The fleet was sailing about 2,527 miles to the destination of La
Rochelle in France, where they are due to arrive on May 16. 
</P>
</TEXT>
