<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK New Airport Experience Program Tickets Sold Out </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong residents have responded
enthusiastically to the five-day opening of the Chek Lap Kok new
airport with all tickets sold out within two days.
</P>
<P>
"The New Airport Experience" program is being sponsored by the
Hong Kong Airport Authority.
</P>
<P>
Clinton Leeks, director of the Corporate Development, said that
62,500 tickets had been available, with 53,000 sold through
branches of the Standard Chartered Bank and the rest snapped up
through group bookings which were made direct by telephone to an
authority hotline.
</P>
<P>
Group bookings were eight times oversubscribed, he said.
</P>
<P>
The new airport will be able to handle up to 35 million
passengers and 3 million tons of cargo a year during its initial
operation. Upon full development in the longer term, the airport
will have an annual throughput capacity of 87 million passengers
and 9 million tons of cargo.
</P>
<P>
Leeks said that he was delighted with this warm response to the
program.
</P>
<P>
"This shows the tremendous level of interest Hong Kong people
have in their new airport. It is very satisfying that after so
many years of hard work by so many we can now show the public just
what has been achieved," he said.
</P>
<P>
However, Leeks said: "our prime task now is to have the airport
ready to begin operations on July 6."
</P>
<P>
Another opportunity for the public to visit the airport will
come on June 21 when the Mass Transit Railway Corporation will
hold its charity ride to mark the opening of its Airport Express,
he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
