<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nigerian Head of State Orders Release of 142 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Nigerian Head of State, General Sani
Abacha has ordered the release of 142 detainees with immediate
effect, said Minister of Internal Affairs Bashir Dalhatu.
</P>
<P>
The move is a fulfilment of Abacha's promise last November,
when he pledged to grant freedom to those whose release will no
longer pose a threat to the peace and security of the country.
</P>
<P>
The Nigerian media, however, Thursday expressed disappointment
over the list of the released, which includes none of the
prominent detainees whose release has been much called for, such
as M.K.O. Abiola, the acclaimed winner of the annulled June 12,
1993 presidential election.
</P>
<P>
Media reports noted that of the 60 persons Pope John II had
asked Abacha to release on his March visit to Nigeria, three are
on the list of the release.
</P>
<P>
According to a statement of Dalhatu distributed at a press
conference in Abuja on Wednesday, the released persons are
convicted prisoners of 60 years old and above, prisoners serving
life sentences, detainees who have been in custody for more than
10 years and those awaiting trial for minor offenses.
</P>
<P>
The statement said the government is determined to
continuously appraise the circumstances of all incarcerated
people with a view to integrating them into the society as
reformed citizens. 
</P>
</TEXT>
