<HEADLINE> China's Foreign Trade Minister Meets Chile's Foreign Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Shi Guangsheng, China's Minister of
Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation, met here today with
visiting Chilean Foreign Minister Jose Miguel Insulza.
</P>
<P>
Shi said that China and Chile are far away from each other in
distance, but have smoothly developed bilateral ties with broad
potential in economic and trade cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government values the development of economic and
trade relations with Chile, Shi said, adding that China also
encourages its entrepreneurs to invest in Chile and jointly
explore South American markets.
</P>
<P>
Insulza said bilateral economic and trade ties have maintained
a sound momentum and the rapid economic development in both China
and his country has provided opportunities for improving bilateral
trade.
</P>
<P>
The World Trade Organization (WTO) needs China, the foreign
minister said, adding that his country supports China's entry to
the WTO as soon as possible. Shi expressed his appreciation for
Chile's support.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the trade volume between China and Chile
hit 977 million U.S. dollars last year, up 6.3 percent; and
exports from were valued at 562 million U.S. dollars, up 21.2
percent.
</P>
<P>
Chile was China's fourth largest trading partner in Latin
America last year, while China was Chile's second largest in
Asia. 
</P>
