<HEADLINE> International Cooperation in Drug Control Stressed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 7 (Xinhua) -- State Councillor Luo Gan said today
that China will actively participate in international cooperation
in cracking down on drug trafficking.
</P>
<P>
Luo's remark came during a meeting with a delegation from the
United Nations Drug Control Program (DCP) led by its executive
director, Pino Arlacchi, who is also deputy secretary-general of
the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
China is among the countries which have suffered the most
historically from drugs, and the Chinese people have exerted great
efforts for 100 years in seeking total elimination of drugs, Luo
said.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the Chinese government's achievements in
both the domestic and the international drug control fields have
not only safeguarded the interest of the Chinese people but also
contributed a lot to the world's overall fight against drugs.
</P>
<P>
China, as a permanent member of the U.N. Security Council, has
always supported the DCP's guiding role in the international drug
control sector, Luo sai, and appreciates the DCP's assistance. The
DCP will continue to receive China's full support in its drug
control strategy, he said.
</P>
<P>
Arlacchi expressed satisfaction with China's cooperation in
recent years. He said China has set a good example for the rest of
the world to follow in fighting drugs, and is able to avoid the
harm of illegal drugs while advancing its social and economic
development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
