<HEADLINE> Philippines Acts to Help Farmers Hit by El Nino </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel Ramos has
ordered agencies concerned to study granting a loan restructuring
or debt moratorium for farmers affected by the El Nino phenomenon,
a presidential press release said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Ramos issued the order to the Department of Agriculture, the
Land Bank of the Philippines and other agencies after receiving
reports of severe decline in farm production in some areas,
especially those hit by the prolonged dry spell.
</P>
<P>
To combat the effects of the El Nino, Ramos also approved the
revision of the crop insurance scheme and the premium rates for
rice and corn of the Philippine Crop Insurance Corporation, the
press release said.
</P>
<P>
It quoted Ramos as saying that the new rates are expected to
"further improve the farmers' access to crop insurance and thereby
promote high agricultural production."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the president was told that the Social Security
Systems and the Government Service Insurance System, the two major
players in the insurance industry, have been urged to increase
fund releases for the distressed areas.
</P>
<P>
The El Nino has brought about famine and outbreaks of diseases
in the southern Philippines. About 3.4 million people have been
affected and at least 80 of them killed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
