<HEADLINE> Consulate-General's Discussions with LegCo Candidates "Inappropriate": Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 7 (Xinhua) -- A spokesman of the Commissioner's
Office of the Chinese Foreign Ministry in Hong Kong said here
Thursday that it is inappropriate for foreign consular offices and
their personnel to get involved in matters concerning the
elections for the first Legislative Council (LegCo) of the Special
Administrative Region (SAR).
</P>
<P>
The spokesman made the statement when commenting on British
consulate-general inviting candidates of the LegCo for discussion.
</P>
<P>
"The election for the first LegCo is entirely an internal
matter within the high degree of autonomy enjoyed by the HKSAR,"
the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The election methods formulated by the HKSAR Government on its
own for the first LegCo are consistent with the relevant
provisions of the Basic Law and the actual conditions in Hong
Kong. These methods have reflected the principle of developing
democracy progressively in Hong Kong, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman noted that preparations for the coming elections
are being carried out "in an orderly manner," and "we are
confident that the HKSAR is capable of making the elections for
its first LegCo a success, and that the elections will be held in
a democratic, fair and open manner."
</P>
<P>
After Hong Kong's return to China, the spokesman added, the
question of Hong Kong is entirely an internal matter of China. In
accordance with Article 55 of Vienna Convention on Consular
Relations and Article 24 of Regulations of the People's Republic
of China on Consular Privileges and Immunities, foreign consular
offices and their personnel shall not interfere in the internal
affairs of the state to which they are accredited.
</P>
<P>
"Accordingly, it is inappropriate for foreign consular offices
and their personnel in Hong Kong to get involved, in whatever way,
in matters concerning the elections for the first Legislative
Council of the HKSAR," the spokesman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
