<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Mixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed mixed Thursday as strong buying
interest emerged in the last few hours when trading was bolstered
by the favorable trade surplus for March.
</P>
<P>
The market regained strength and rebounded in the second
session following the announcement that Malaysia's trade surplus
increased by 49.2 percent to 3.72 billion ringgit (about 1
billion U.S. dollars) in March this year from 2.5 billion ringgit
(about 675.675 million U.S. dollars) one month earlier.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index rose 2.21
points to 586.83, the all-share Emas Index firmed 0.57 of a point
to 148.08, the Industrial Index added 8.66 points to 1,090.58
while the Second Board Index eased 1.98 points to 126.19.
</P>
<P>
Gainers led losers by 384 to 274 while 136 were unchanged and
123 others untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover increased to 175.069 million shares valued
at 507.539 million ringgit (about 132 million U.S. dollars) from
145.473 million shares worth 384.724 million ringgit (about
100.058 million U.S. dollars) on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The main board turnover rose to 163.947 million shares valued
at 490.211 million ringgit (about 127.493 million U.S. dollars)
from 133.024 million shares worth 365.899 million ringgit (about
95.162 million U.S. dollars) on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The second board turnover eased to 11.122 million shares valued
at 17.327 million ringgit (about 4.506 million U.S. dollars) from
Wednesday's 12.449 million shares worth 18.825 million ringgit
(about 4.895 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Off-market volume shrunk to 3.620 million shares valued at
13.546 million ringgit (about 3.523 million U.S. dollars) from
5.120 million shares worth 15.069 million ringgit (about 3.919
million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
On a sectoral basis, consumer products accounted for 8.487
million shares traded on the main board, industrial products
14.840 million shares, construction 15.712 million shares,
trading/service 52.611 million shares, infrastructure 585,000
shares, finance 35.736 million shares, hotels 501,000 shares,
properties 11.518 million shares, plantation 7.605 million shares,
mining 490,400 shares, trusts 96,000 shares, closed/fund 175,000
shares, and loans 15.588 million shares. 
</P>
</TEXT>
