<HEADLINE> Talks Between Government, Striking Nurses Fail </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Talks between the government and
striking nurses in New Delhi did not yield any result and the
strike would continue in the city, a Delhi Nurses Union (DNU)
spokesperson said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Nurses gathered in front of the Health Ministry headquarters in
large numbers and raised anti-government slogans following the
failure of talks, which were held here Thursday morning.
</P>
<P>
The nurses would not relent unless the government agreed to a
hike in their pay scales, which the spokesperson claimed were the
lowest in the country vis-a-vis their qualifications.
</P>
<P>
Medical services in the capital remained paralyzed for the
third day Thursday. City Health Minister Harsh Vardhan warned
Wednesday against harsh measures if the nurses remained
indifferent to the woes of the patients.
</P>
<P>
The strike, which started here Tuesday, has been called by DNU
to protest against the backtracking by the government on the
agreement signed with it in last September on pay scales and other
demands. The government has said that it was open for talks with
agitating nurses over their demands, but ruled out any pay hike.
</P>
