<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaysia to Report on Technical Cooperation in G-15 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia will report to the
Group of 15 (G-15) Trade and Economic Ministers Meeting in Cairo
Friday on technical cooperation programs, according to an
official announcement Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia will also distribute a Compendium of Technical
Cooperation Programs available in the grouping, the Ministry of
International Trade and Industry (MITI) said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia agreed to undertake the job at the first G-15 Trade
and Economic Ministers Meeting held in Kuala Lumpur last year when
the G-15 summit was also held here.
</P>
<P>
The information collected is expected to be useful to members
in identifying programs and activities they could participate as
part of efforts to assist each other in development and growth,
MITI said.
</P>
<P>
The Second G-15 Trade and Economic Ministers Meeting will be
held in conjunction with the VIII G-15 Summit from next Monday
until Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The agenda for the economic ministers' meeting includes issues
related to World Trade Organization (WTO) and the Second WTO
Ministerial Conference; impact of developments in international
financial and capital markets; and follow-up to the Kuala Lumpur
meeting on G-15 cooperation in trade and investment in the areas
of technical cooperation, standards, bilateral agreements and
private sector cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The impact of the Asian financial crisis on trade and
development will also feature in the discussions.
</P>
<P>
MITI said Malaysia is also setting up a National Pavilion at
the G-15 Trade Exhibition and Business Workshop, which will be
held from Friday until next Wednesday, in conjunction with the
Summit.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia will also participate in a business workshop with a
country presentation on Malaysia's trade and investment policies
and economic prospects, it said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
