<HEADLINE> China Urges Britain Not To Interfere in China's Affairs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 7 (Xinhua) -- China's Foreign Ministry spokesman
Zhu Bangzao here today urged the British government to
"immediately stop the interference in the election of the
Legislative Council (Legco) of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR)."
</P>
<P>
Zhu made the remark in response to a question on the British HK
Consulate General's meeting with certain candidates of Hong Kong's
first Legco. The election will be held in late May.
</P>
<P>
According to Zhu, it is widely reported that the British HKSAR
Consulate General recently invited several Legco candidates to
discuss the future election. "It is the direct interference in the
affairs of HKSAR," he said, adding that the move "violates the
Joint Declaration signed by the two governments and arouses
adverse affections from the Hong Kong people and press."
</P>
<P>
Zhu urged the British government to stop such action and
strictly observe the Joint Declaration for the sound development
of Sino-British ties.  
</P>
