<HEADLINE> Russian Government to Be Finalized Friday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Russian Prime Minister Sergei
Kiriyenko said Thursday that the formation of the Russian
government will be finalized on Friday.
</P>
<P>
During the first meeting of the recognized cabinet, Kiriyenko
said that President Boris Yeltsin and he will wrap up Friday their
discussion on the structure and the appointments of new ministers.
</P>
<P>
So far, three deputy prime ministers and 17 ministers have been
appointed.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Kiriyenko said that throughout the process to select
ministers, both he and Yeltsin maintained active contacts with
members of parliament and tried to take into consideration their
proposals on forming the government.
</P>
<P>
The process was based "not on a political but on a professional
approach in selecting personnel," said Kiriyenko, who was
confirmed as the prime minister on April 24 by the State Duma, or
lower house of the parliament.
</P>
<P>
Former Prime Minister Victor Chernomyerdin and his cabinet were
dismissed by Yeltsin on March 23, which led to a month-long
government crisis in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
