<HEADLINE> Macao Governor Vows to Maintain Social Order </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Macao Governor Vasco Rocha Vieira has
pledged that his government will strengthen the police forces to
maintain social order in the territory.
</P>
<P>
He said at a weekly police forces meeting on Wednesday that his
government will "continue to provide the police forces with all
the help they need to fulfill their mission for the safety and
well-being of the Macao population."
</P>
<P>
Macao police launched a series of actions in the past week,
detaining dozens of suspects of murder and bombing cases, and
seizing a batch of firearms and explosives.
</P>
<P>
The Macao Daily News reported on Thursday that the governor
expressed his support to the way by which the police forces have
been carrying out their duties.
</P>
<P>
The report said he "reiterated his appreciation and praise for
the police forces efforts and reaffirmed his support and
solidarity."
</P>
<P>
Since the beginning of the year, at least seven civil servants,
including several of middle and senior ranks, were either murdered
or attacked. The police fought back last week and detained an
alleged triad boss, who has since been on pre-trial detention in
jail. 
</P>
