<HEADLINE> Macao Unemployment Rate Rises Slightly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Earlier figures show that there were about 5,700 people above
the age 14 without jobs in Macao at the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
The underemployment rate rose to 1.5 percent, 0.2 percent
higher than the December-February period. It was a rise of 0.9
percent from the January-March period in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Macao has suffered an economic slowdown since 1993. The
economic growth rate for 1997 was estimated at less than one
percent. 
