<HEADLINE> Over 5,000 Ugandans Infected with Sleeping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, May 7 (Xinhua) -- At least 5,000 Ugandans have been
infected with sleeping sickness in the north-west, an official
has said.
</P>
<P>
Obiga Kania, a local member of parliament from Arua District
in north-western Uganda, said only Doctor Without Borders, a
French non-government organization, was collecting patients in
his district for treatment, media here reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
He urged local authorities to react.
</P>
<P>
The overgrowing grass in Inyau River bed in the district has
formed a breeding site for tsetse flies which spread the disease,
Kania complained.
</P>
<P>
Some people have been infected twice in recent three weeks due to
high density of tsetse flies, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Sleeping sickness was rampant before mid eighties. The report from
Arua is the first of its kind in recent years on the sickness in the
country. 
</P>
