<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to List Third Investment Fund </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 7 (Xinhua) -- China will list its third securities
investment fund on the Shanghai Stock Exchange on Friday, marking
a fresh move in its effort to develop institutional investors.
</P>
<P>
Fund Xinghua, China's third investment fund after Fund Jintai
and Fund Kaiyuan, has two billion units at a face value of 1 yuan
each.
</P>
<P>
The sponsors of the new fund -- Beijing-based Huaxia Securities
Co. Ltd., Beijing Securities Co. Ltd. and China Science and
Technology International Trust and Investment Co. Ltd. -- have
purchased 60 million units, with the remaining 1.94 billion units
offered to the public.
</P>
<P>
The closed-end fund, under the custody of the China
Construction Bank and managed by the Huaxia Fund Management
Co. Ltd., has a term of 15 years and will invest 80 percent of its
capital in stocks and the other 20 percent in state treasury bonds.
</P>
<P>
China's first two investment funds, Fund Jintai and Fund
Kaiyuan, met with great investor enthusiasm immediately after they
were listed on the Shanghai and Shenzhen exchanges on April 7.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Zhengqing, chairman of the China Securities Regulatory
Committee, said that China will issue two more securities
investment funds this year.
</P>
<P>
Currently, China has nearly 800 listed companies and more than
32 million stock investors.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
