<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-07 10:26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 51.5 Kilograms of Heroin Seized in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Turkish police has seized 51.5
kilograms of heroin during an anti-drug operation in Bilecik
province in western Turkey, the semi-official Anatolia News Agency
reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The news agency said that the police searched a car in the
center of the province on Thursday and found the heroin in
parcels hidden in the vehicle.
</P>
<P>
The driver, named Sefer Ozcanan and other four people in
connection with the drug smuggling have been detained, said the
agency.
</P>
<P>
Turkey is on the transit route of drug trafficking to
Europe from the border areas of Afghanistan and Pakistan. In
1996, Turkish police seized 4.4 tonnes of heroin, which
accounted for 40 percent of the world's total haul.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
