<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Continue to Decline on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Share prices declined further on
the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times Industrials
Index (STII) fell sharply by 21.755 points to close at 1426.65
points on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume was thin at 99.54 million units, valued
at 184.94 million Singapore dollars (about 114.16 million U.S.
dollars). Declines overwhelmed advances by 239 to 36, while 319
other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
RHB Capital Warrant99 was the most actively traded stock as it
registered a turnover of 13.92 million units. It was followed by
Renong which had 11.69 million shares traded. Rekapac was next
with 10.97 million units changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Local car distributor Cycle &AMP; Carriage (C&AMP;C) led the gainers of
the day as it rose by 30 cents to finish at 6.4 Singapore dollars.
DBS (Development Bank of Singapore) Foreign and OCBC (Overseas
Chinese Banking Corporation) Foreign increased by 20 cents each to
end at ten and 6.65 Singapore dollars respectively. UOB (United
Overseas Bank) was up by 15 cents to close at 6.25 Singapore
dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, SPH (Singapore Press Holdings) was the biggest
loser as it declined by 90 cents to end at 16.1 Singapore dollars.
GE Life fell by 50 cents to close at 11.5 Singapore dollars, while
OUB (Overseas Union Bank) Foreign lost 45 cents to finish at 5.35
Singapore dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
