<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bountiful Flowers Beautify, Benefit Plateau Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Xining, capital of Qinghai Province,
is in fine bloom this spring as colorful tulips, elegant peonies
and fragrant lilacs are blossoming.
</P>
<P>
The highland city is only one of the places in Qinghai on the
Qinghai-Tibet Plateau benefiting from a booming flower industry.
</P>
<P>
People in Qinghai have a long-standing love for flowers and the
province's plentiful sunshine and sharp differences between
daytime and night-time temperatures are suited for growing
flowers. However, flower-growing long had been a family business.
</P>
<P>
With constant improvements in the living standard, more and
more people began to look for flowers in marketplaces for
weddings, festivals, or for hospital patients.
</P>
<P>
Seizing the opportunity, shrewd business people in the province
have built more than 1,000 flower-growing centers with a combined
annual capacity of more than 500,000 flowers, and opened a dozen
flower markets.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
