<DOCNO> XIE19980507.0170 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Ethnic Minority Area Expects To Get More Foreign Funds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, May 7 (Xinhua) -- The Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region,
the largest region of ethnic minorities in China, plans to use 168
million US dollars worth of foreign investment this year.
</P>
<P>
Of that, 128 million US dollars will be in the form of loans,
and the remainder will be direct foreign investment, said
Abul'ahat Abdurixit, chairman of the regional people's government.
</P>
<P>
The money will be used for farms, water conservation projects,
and the textile and manufacturing industries.
</P>
<P>
Xinjiang covers a sixth of China's territory and its 5,400-km
border runs along eight countries. The region is China's largest
cotton producer and has 2.4 billion tons of proven oil reserves.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, the central government has shifted its
emphasis of economic development from coastal areas to the central
and western parts of the country and Xinjiang has major
attractions for overseas investors. In the past five years, it has
held five foreign trade fairs, where 815 contracts were signed,
worth 1.1 billion US dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
