<HEADLINE> Large Lead, Zinc Deposits Found in North China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, May 7 (Xinhua) -- A large field containing
rich lead and zinc deposits has been found in Longhua County of
north China's Hebei Province.
</P>
<P>
The proven reserves are estimated at one million tons,
according to local sources.
</P>
<P>
The field, which also contains other minerals including
sulphur and molybdenum, can be turned into eight mining zones
in accordance with the distribution of mineral resources.
</P>
<P>
The mine will be able to produce more than 100,000 tons of
refined lead and zinc ore powder a year, with the concentration of
lead and zinc amounting to 10 percent.
</P>
<P>
Experts say that the field can sustain 50 years of development
and the full investment should be recovered five years after the
mine begins production. 
</P>
</TEXT>
