<DOCNO> XIE19980507.0189 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Makes Progress in New and Renewable Energy Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 7 (Xinhua) -- China has made progress in
developing new and renewable energy from water, solar, wind,
geothermal and tidal sources, according to a senior official with
the State Development Planning Commission.
</P>
<P>
To date, the country's annual utilization rate of new and
renewable energy has reached 300 million tons of standard coal,
accounting for a quarter of the national consumption of primary
energy and more than 47 percent of energy consumption in rural
areas, the official said.
</P>
<P>
The country has made world-renowned progress in small
hydropower utilization. Nearly 7,000 small hydropower stations
have been set up with an installed capacity of 20 million
kilowatts (kw), generating more than 50 billion kilowatts/hour
(kwh) of electricity, accounting for 25 percent of the total that
can be exploited.
</P>
<P>
Some 75 percent of rural households in China have installed
coal-saving stoves. More than 5.7 million rural households used
bio-gas with an annual bio-gas production of 1.5 billion cubic
meters.
</P>
<P>
In terms of using the solar energy, there were 5 million square
meters of solar heaters, 6 million square meters of passive
solar-heated housing, 40,000 square meters of solar greenhouses
for agricultural uses and 150,000 solar stoves.
</P>
<P>
Wind energy has been used for major electricity generation. To
date, 160,000 household mini- and small-size wind generators are
in use with a combined capacity of 15,000 kw, mostly distributed
in the remote pastoral areas, mountain areas and islands. China
has imported medium- and large-size wind generators from Denmark,
the Netherlands, and the United States to equip 15 power plants
which have 120 generating units with a capacity of 30,000 kw.
</P>
<P>
China is also rich in tidal energy, 90 percent of which is
located in Zhejiang and Fujian provinces. Some 10 tidal-power
stations have been set up nationwide with a total installed
capacity of 7,000 kw.
</P>
<P>
The reserves of small coal mines that can be exploited reach
more than 10 billion tons. The reserves have been mined for more
than 500 million tons of coal annually, making up 40 percent of
the national raw coal production.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
