<HEADLINE> China's Jiangxi Increases Investment to Boost Economic Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, May 7 (Xinhua) -- East China's Jiangxi Province will
increase investment this year to spur economic growth, according
to official sources.
</P>
<P>
Jiangxi's investment in fixed assets this year is expected to
be 16.5 percent up on last year, according to the provincial
government.
</P>
<P>
Jiangxi is set to achieve an economic growth rate of 8 percent
this year and will, moreover, strive for a rate as high as 11
percent, Governor Shu Shengyou said.
</P>
<P>
"To achieve the goals, we have increased investment on the
basis of economic restructuring," Shu said.
</P>
<P>
More funds will be invested in water conservation, energy,
transportation, telecommunications, environmental protection and
technical innovation, Shu added. He called on the state-owned
enterprises and overseas-funded and privately-run enterprises to
increase investment.
</P>
<P>
Jiangxi has raised 53.4 billion yuan for 74 key projects in the
last five years, 41 of which have already been completed.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the projects has considerably reduced the
effects of such "bottleneck" sectors as power, railways and
highways, experts said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
