<HEADLINE> Vietnam Decree Sets Stock Market Rules </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam will promulgate a decree on
securities and stock markets this month, the Vietnam News Agency
(VNA) reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The agency quoted Chairman of Vietnam's State Securities
Commission Le Van Chau as saying the decree will be the first
legal document for the establishment and operations of stock
markets in Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
The draft decree was officially approved by the Vietnamese
government at its regular session in late April.
</P>
<P>
Under the decree, the State Securities Commission will be in
charge of granting licenses to stock trading and brokerage
companies.
</P>
<P>
Chau said a number of commercial banks are in the process of
setting up subsidiary stock trading companies with investment
consultancy sections and other departments.
</P>
<P>
Foreigners will be able to become involved in transactions on
the stock market in conformity with domestic investment laws, and
the measure of their involvement will be decided by the Vietnamese
government, he added.
</P>
<P>
Foreigners will be entitled to partake in stock transactions by
purchasing shares in equity enterprises, or by buying long-term
bonds issued by commercial banks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
