<HEADLINE> Acupuncture Doctors Looking Into One Particular Chinese Method </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Doctors of acupuncture gathered
recently for an international symposium in the Chinese city of
Tianjin to get a closer look at one particular method created by a
Chinese professor of medicine.
</P>
<P>
Doctors and scholars from 18 countries attended the symposium,
which was hosted by the No. 1 Hospital of Tianjin's College of
Traditional Chinese Medicine.
</P>
<P>
Professor Shi Xuemin, the head of the hospital, demonstrated
lthe method for treating apoplexy, constipation, anuresis,
incontinence, shoulder problems, dysphagia, and other problems and
diseases.
</P>
<P>
Doctors in some 90 foreign countries have adopted this
particular method in treating their patients, and some countries
like Japan, the Republic of Korea, and the United States have
organized groups to study the method.
</P>
<P>
According to some statistics, about 15 million people have
received acupuncture treatments in the United States, which has
more than 10,000 practitioners. 
</P>
