<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Injured Sammer Pulls out of German Squad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Germany libero Matthias Sammer said he
decided to pull out of the World Cup finals starting on June 10 in
France because of a lingering knee injury.
</P>
<P>
The Borussia Dortmund defender is struggling to recover from
surgery last October on his troublesome left knee.
</P>
<P>
Sammer, who earned 51 caps for Germany, is regarded as one of
the finest liberos since Franz Beckenbauer. 
</P>
