<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambian Anti-Drug Officer Sacked </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, May 7 (Xinhua) -- A Zambian anti-drug officer has been
sacked for alleged corrupt practices and falsehood, Zambia Daily
Mail reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper quoted Mukutulu Sinyani, Senior Assistant
Commissioner and Spokesperson of the Drug Enforcement Commission
(DEC), as saying here Wednesday that DEC has terminated the
employment of Lawrece Chongo, former Assistant Investigations
Officer of the commission, for alleged discreditable conduct.
</P>
<P>
He said that the commission expects highest standards of
discipline and credibility among its officers to avoid
compromising operations.
</P>
<P>
The commission will only engage corrupt free minded persons to
fight the drug scourge, he said.
</P>
<P>
Sinyani said that DEC will not allow anyone to dent its good
image and warned other officers involved in such inconceivable
vices to stop before the axe falls on them.
</P>
<P>
He called on the public to report any DEC officers working
against the commission's objectives of freeing the country from
drug war.
</P>
<P>
"Any person who has credible information on the conduct of any
officer which could lead to tarnishing the image of our country
should feel free to report to the nearest police or drug
enforcement commission officer," Sinyani said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
