<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Urbanites Prefer Quick-frozen Foods </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 7 (Xinhua) -- More than 50 percent of the Chinese
urbanites prefer quick-frozen foods, especially frozen dumplings,
according to a survey released here today.
</P>
<P>
The survey conducted by the State Statistics Bureau shows that
54 percent of urban families prefer quick-frozen food items. Of
that number, 80 percent chose frozen dumplings.
</P>
<P>
The other favorite frozen items are stuffed dumplings, steamed
stuffed buns, won ton and steamed buns.
</P>
<P>
In different cities, the family preferences are
different. Seventy-two percent of families in Fuzhou, capital of
east China's Fujian Province, prefer frozen food, while the ratio
for Shenyang, capital of northeast China's Liaoning Province, is
48 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
