<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladesh's Development Program Progresses Slowly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh's annual development
program (ADP) has been progressing slowly due to constraints in
fund release, lack of cooperation and proper policy guidelines and
some other reasons, an English daily reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Financial Express quoted officials concerned as saying that
the reasons for the lower pace also include delay in preparation,
revision and approval of projects, lack of manpower, delay in
appointment of consultants and settlement of tender documents, and
problems in acquisition of land.
</P>
<P>
The paper said the government funded 63.7 billion taka (1.38
billion U.S. dollars), or half of the ADP's total budget in the
first nine months of fiscal 1997-98 (July, 1997-July, 1998), 6
percent less than that of the same period of the last fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
The amount spent during the same period of the last fiscal year
was 70.05 billion taka (1.52 billion dollars), 56 percent of the
total ADP budget of 125 billion taka (2.72 billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
The ADP includes a total of 1,240 projects, of which 48 are
identified as high priority projects, the report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980507.0212 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 28 Killed in Election-Related Violence in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, May 7 (Xinhua) -- An opposition candidate was shot dead
in the southern Philippines on Thursday, bringing to 28 the total
number of people killed in election-related violence.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine News Agency reported that the victim, running
for councilor under the banner of the Laban ng Makabayang Masang
Pilipino (Fight of Patriotic Filipino Masses), was killed by two
unidentified gunmen who opened fire from a vehicle in Sultan
Kudarat, Maguindanao province.
</P>
<P>
The report said two other people were seriously wounded in the
incident, suffering multiple gunshot wounds in the body.
</P>
<P>
The killers fled away. Local police were looking into the
possible motive behind the shooting, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The Commission on Elections and the military have identified
about 406 "sensitive areas" which are violence-prone and need the
protection provided by the military and the police forces.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that 169 people were killed in violence in the
1992 national elections and 210 in the 1995 congressional
elections.
</P>
<P>
The Philippines will hold its national and local polls on May
11. 
</P>
</TEXT>
