<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Success Manifested Everyday in HK: Tung Chee Hwa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa of
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region on Thursday lauded the
continued success of Hong Kong after its return to China, saying,
"The success is manifested everyday in Hong Kong and in every
possible way."
</P>
<P>
Calling 1997 an extraordinary year for the territory, Tung said
at the ongoing annual Corporate Conference of Asia Society, "July
1 saw the smooth and seamless return of Hong Kong to China,
thereby ending 157 years of colonial rule." "Indeed, the people of
Hong Kong had looked forward to this great occasion with immense
pride."
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that Hong Kong people are confident in managing
their future. "The ultimate source of our confidence is the solid
promises of the constitutional document, our Basic Law."
</P>
<P>
To ensure that Hong Kong's international and cosmopolitan
outlook is maintained, Tung continued, "we will continue to
assimilate the knowledge and experiences of the West while we
preserve the virtues of Chinese culture."
</P>
<P>
"If there has been any changes at all in Hong Kong since the
handover, it is the mindset of our people," he pointed out. "Hong
Kong is no longer an enclave economy with an artificial and
psychological barrier created by the date of June 30, 1997, and
the border between Hong Kong and the mainland of China."
</P>
<P>
Tung noted that in the immediate years before the handover and
during 1997, tens of thousands of Hong Kong people who had
previously migrated overseas returned home. "They feel the pride,
they sense the opportunity and they want to participate in
building a better tomorrow," he declared.  
</P>
</TEXT>
