<HEADLINE> Traffic Accidents Kill 18 Zimbabweans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Eighteen Zimbabweans died and 103
others were hurt in two separate accidents involving three buses
and a haulage truck near Featherstone in Kadoma of Central
Zimbabwe, an influential daily newspaper said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Seven people were killed and over 50 others were injured, 10
of them seriously, when a long-distance bus collided head-on with
a trans-border haulage truck near Featherstone along the
Harare-Masvingo highway Tuesday night, The Herald reported.
</P>
<P>
Eleven people were killed while 53 others were injured, six of
them seriously, when two mini-buses collided at a narrow bridge
near Venice Mine in Kadoma Tuesday afternoon, the police reported
Wednesday night.
</P>
