<HEADLINE> Northwestern China Improving Investment Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Ningxia Hui
Autonomous region is making efforts to improve its investment
environment, develop foreign trade, and increase cooperation with
the eastern part of China, according to Ma Qizhi, the region's
acting chairman.
</P>
<P>
Ma told a recent conference that Ningxia had over 300 million
US dollars worth of exports and imports last year, registering an
annual increase of 18.6 percent. The increase in exports was 17.4
percent, much higher than the country's average.
</P>
<P>
In the past five years, the region approved over 400
overseas-funded projects and used 240 million US dollars worth of
investment.
</P>
<P>
Exports of overseas-funded enterprises accounted for 14 percent
of the region's total last year.
</P>
<P>
Ma says that, using its resource advantages, the region has
established exports centers for 370 products like metals, coal,
and cashmere.
</P>
<P>
Ningxia has also found ways to cooperate with other areas in
technical and economic fields and developed more than 500 projects
with eastern provinces over the past five years.
</P>
<P>
With the capital city of Yinchuan as the center of opening up,
Ningxia has formed a new economic structure based on resources and
raw materials.
</P>
<P>
Tourism has also been developed over the past five years, and
there have been over eight million domestic and overseas tourists,
bringing nearly 700 million yuan in revenues. 
</P>
</TEXT>
