<HEADLINE> Xinhua World Economic News Summary at 0600 GMT, May 7 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA -- Indonesia's inflation rate in April slowed to 4.7
percent from 5.49 percent in March, but the cumulative increase in
the consumer price index was 33.09 percent for the first four
months of 1998.
</P>
<P>
Inflation pressures would likely intensify in the coming months
following the hefty hikes in fuel and electricity prices announced
by the government this week, Minister of Information Alwi Dahlan
said on Wednesday after a monthly cabinet meeting.
(Indonesia-Inflation)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CARACAS -- Venezuela's oil revenue this year will drop by some
three billion U.S. dollars when the crude price averages between
13-13.5 dollars per barrel, a Venezuelan expert predicted.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the "El Globo" journal, analyst Felix
Rossi Guerrero said he did not believe the oil price would soar up
to 15 dollars per barrel soon. (Venezuela-Oil Price)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BANGKOK -- The value in baht of Thailand's rice exports during
the first four months this year soared by 243.5 percent to 33.6
billion baht, according to figures released by the Foreign Trade
Department of the Thai Commerce Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Compared with the first four months of last year, the dollar
value of the shipments rose by 26.7 percent to 750 million
U.S. dollars, based on the average exchange rate of 44.8 baht for
the dollar for the period. (Thailand-Rice Export)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
PANAMA CITY -- The Inter-American Development Bank (IADB)
Wednesday announced a grant of 250 million U.S. dollars to Panama
in loans and donations earmarked for social works.
</P>
<P>
The grant will be mainly channeled to the education sector for
projects including school rehabilitation and teacher training,
said Camalle Gaskin Reyes, IADB representative in Panama.
(Panama-IADB-Grant)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO -- The Uruguayan trade deficit reached 105 million
U.S. dollars in January, the central bank said in a report
released Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The deficit resulted from 285 million dollars in imports which
surpassed the 180 million dollars in exports.
(Uruguay-Trade Deficit)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WELLINGTON -- The eastern part of New Zealand's North Island
could become the country's another major gasfield as a test well
there has shown "commercial success," the Wellington newspaper the
Dominion reported on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Enerco company has drilled its first test well, which
produced 325,000 cubic meters of gas a day. But it believed that
the potential could reach two million cubic meters a day.
(New Zealand-Gasfield)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BOGOTA -- The national committee of colombian coffee sellers
froze the price of 125 kilogram bag of coffee at 300,000 pesos
(about 218.6 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The new price represents a four percent reduction as compared
with the previous price of 312,875 pesos, which was in force since
April 28. (Colombia-Coffee Price) 
