<HEADLINE> Bogota Soccer Fans Injured as Stand Collapses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, May 6 (Xinhua) -- At least 25 soccer fans were injured
when part of a Bogota sports stadium collapsed during a match
between the capital's two top teams on Wednesday evening.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred about 25 minutes into the match as fans
celebrated the Millionarios team's first goal against rivals
Santafe.
</P>
<P>
The injured fell between two and three meters onto seats below
when a barrier in an upper part of a stand in the northern part of
the stadium gave way as spectators pushed forward.
</P>
<P>
Ambulances ferried the wounded to hospitals in the area.
</P>
<P>
The match continued uninterrupted but police cordoned off the
damaged section of the stadium and helped evacuate fans. 
</P>
</TEXT>
