<HEADLINE> Dhaka to Receive U.S. Grant for Aquatic Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh will receive 5 million U.S.
dollars in grant from the United States for the management of an
aquatic eco-systems through community husbandry project, the
United News of Bangladesh (UNB) reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Implementation of the five-year project will begin on October 1
to promote ecologically-sound management of flood-plain resources,
like fisheries and other wetland products, to ensure sustainable
food supply to poor communities in the country, according to an
agreement signed here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The main objective of the project is to demonstrate how to
increase the number and kinks of fish in selected flood-plain
areas and to improve the access of the rural poor to these sites.
</P>
</TEXT>
