<DOCNO> XIE19980507.0261 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia to Reforest in East Kalimantan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, May 7 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian government should
allocate at least 850 billion rupiah (106 million U.S. dollars) to
rehabilitate the 500,000 hectares of forest ravaged by fires in
East Kalimantan in the last three months, a forestry official
said.
</P>
<P>
"We need about 1.6 million to 2.2 million rupiah to
rehabilitate every hectare of the burned forest," Director General
of Supervision at the Forest and Plantation Ministry Oesman Yoesep
said Wednesday in the East Kalimantan capital of Samarinda,
according to reports reaching here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Yoesep said it will take dozens of years to rehabilitate the
burned forest, following the fires which have caused economic
losses of 9.371 trillion rupiah (1.7 billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
According to Yoesep, of the 500,000 hectares of razed area,
some 306,000 hectares are located on forest concession holders'
land.
</P>
<P>
He said the local forestry office has been providing 29.9
billion rupiah for labor-intensive projects involving forest
rehabilitation, forest society development and agro-forestry
intensification.  
</P>
</TEXT>
