<HEADLINE> Tibet Developing Compulsory Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAHSA, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Eleven of the Tibet Autonomous
Region's 75 counties now have universal 6-year mandatory education.
</P>
<P>
The 11 counties have a combined population of 530,000,
accounting for one fifth of Tibet's population.
</P>
<P>
A local education official says that Tibet has a comprehensive
education system from elementary and secondary education to higher
education and professional and adult education.
</P>
<P>
Its elementary education system has improved in the past seven
years and now gives 73.5 percent of the school-aged children a
chance to attend school, a 26.5 percent increase from 1991.
</P>
<P>
The autonmous regional government will have a three-year
education project to make 6-year mandatory education universal in
35 counties, he said, and when it is completed by 2000, over 80
percent of all the school-aged children in Tibet will have the
opportunity to attend school. 
</P>
</TEXT>
