<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rios Ousted by Ferreira at Hamburg Open Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, May 6 (Xinhua) -- Chilean Marcelo Rios, who briefly
replaced American Peter Sampras as the world number one earlier
this year, suffered a three-set defeat against South African Wayne
Ferreira in the second round of the Hamburg Open tennis tounament
on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Coming back from an elbow injury which dropped his ATP rangking
to number three, top seed Rios lost out to Ferreira 3-6, 6-4, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Number three seed Thomas Muster of Austria ousted Russian
Yevgeny Kafelnikov 6-4, 6-2 in a battle of two former French Open
champions, while number seven Richard Krajicek beat fellow
Dutchman Sjeng Schalken 7-6 (8-6), 6-2.
</P>
<P>
Two seeded Spaniards also advanced. Eight-seeded Alberto
Berasategui defeated Swede Magnus Gustafsson 6-3, 6-3 and will
next meet number nine Felix Mantilla, who beat German Bohdan
Ulihrach 6-4, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
In two late matches, sixteen-seeded Croat Goran Ivanisevic beat
Nicolas Lapentti of Italy 4-6, 6-1, 6-4, while Hicham Arazi of
Morocco upset 12th-seeded Briton Tim Henman 6-3, 6-3. 
</P>
</TEXT>
