<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Clashes Occur in Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, May 6 (Xinhua) -- Several blood-shedding conflicts
occurred Wednesday in Kosovo, a troubled province of Serbia,
leaving four dead and at least two injured, the Yugoslav news
agency Tanjug reported.
</P>
<P>
Armed ethnic Albanians ambushed a police patrol car in
Mitrovica, Kosovo, at 00:45 a.m. (local time) Wednesday, killing
one policeman and injuring two others. One attacker was killed in
the exchange of fire.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Two ethnic Albanians were found dead in the Decanska
Bistrica River Wednesday morning. The Serb police said that they
were executed by Kosovo separatists for "collaborating" with
Serbian authorities.
</P>
<P>
A group of armed ethnic Albanian separatists reportedly
attacked Yugoslav frontier guards in the Djakovica area bordering
Albania at 11:30 a.m. but were defeated.
</P>
<P>
Kosovo, where most of the residents are ethnic Albanians,
plunged into chaos since February this year as ethnic Albanian
separatists intensified their campaign for the independence of the
province. 
</P>
</TEXT>
