<HEADLINE> General Merchandise Fair In Northeastern Chinese City Of Dalian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, May 7 (Xinhua) -- The China National Spring Fair of
general merchandise will run in Dalian, a port city in China's
Liaoning Province, from May 8 to 11.
</P>
<P>
The fair will have at least 600 booths, a 39 percent increase
from the previous fair, and 12,000 commodity items will be on
display.
</P>
<P>
Representatives of wholesale and retail companies, and
industrial and commercial enterprises from across China, and from
dozens of overseas companies from Japan, the Republic of Korea,
the United States, Germany, Singapore, and elsewhere will be
present at the fair, according to information provided by the
fair's organizers.
</P>
<P>
The fair is being sponsored by the China General Merchandise
and Commerce Association and is being supported by two
conglomerates in Dalian, the organizers say. 
</P>
