<HEADLINE> Russia Keeps Unbeaten at Ice Hockey Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, May 6 (Xinhua) -- Olympic silver medallists Russia
overwhelmed Finland, winners of the bronze medal in Nagano Winter
Olympics, 4-2 at the World Pool A Ice Hockey Championship in
Switzerland on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Russia topped the Group D standings with six points after three
matches while Finland finished second with four points. Latvia
beat Kazakhstan 7-2 in another match of the group.
</P>
