<HEADLINE> Indonesia Inflation at 33 Percent in 1st Four Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's inflation rate in April
slowed to 4.7 percent from 5.49 percent in March, but the
cumulative increase in the consumer price index was 33.09 percent
for the first four months of 1998.
</P>
<P>
Inflation pressures would likely intensify in the coming months
following the hefty hikes in fuel and electricity prices announced
by the government this week, Minister of Information Alwi Dahlan
said on Wednesday after a monthly cabinet meeting.
</P>
<P>
According to the Central Bureau of Statistics, the price of
food jumped 5.91 percent month-on-month in April, while processed
food and cigarette prices rose 7.68 percent, Antara News Agency
reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Housing costs went up 2.29 percent, clothing 4.43 percent,
health 5.29 percent, education and recreation 1.5 percent and
transportation and communication 4.94 percent, it said.
</P>
<P>
Alwi said President Soeharto has called for greater efforts to
curb inflation.
</P>
<P>
Economic observers here predicted that Indonesia's 1998
inflation rate may reach 80 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
