<HEADLINE> Maldini yet to Decide on Baggio </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, May 6 (Xinhua) -- Italian coach Cesare Maldini admitted
Roberto Baggio as "an excellent player" on Wednesday but said he
is yet to decide on his place in the national World Cup squad.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with "Borghese Weekly", the Italian boss
appeared to have been impressed by Baggio's recent outstanding
form and acknowledged that "he's had a good season".
</P>
<P>
The 1994 World Cup hero, who has already hit 19 goals in Serie
A this season, is now desperately fighting for a chance to play in
this summer's French World Cup.
</P>
<P>
Maldini said only few players had now booked their spots in his
22-man list which he must announce before June 2nd the deadline.
</P>
<P>
When asked about the weak points in his squad, Maldini said,
"We have lost an important player in the defence zone and he is
Juventus' Ciro Ferrara. We haven't found quality replacement in
that slot yet."
</P>
<P>
Ferrara has been ruled out of the World Cup because of a broken
leg. 
</P>
