<HEADLINE> Largest Bookstore in China to Open Soon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Beijing residents will soon have a
new place to buy books when China's largest bookstore opens
to the public on May 18, today's China Daily reported.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing Book Center, located at Xidan along the Chang'an
Avenue, will sell 100,000 kinds of books, said Wang Hongjing,
general manager of the center.
</P>
<P>
The center, covering an area of 50,000 sq. m., has eight
stories above ground and three stories underground. Books, audio
and video products will be sold from the ground floor to the
fourth floor.
</P>
<P>
Investment for the construction of the center totals 400
million yuan (48 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
"The center will try to offer people with plenty of food for
thought," Wang said. The center has established contact with about
500 publishing houses around the country.
</P>
<P>
The center will use a computer network, developed by the Taiji
Corp under the North China Computer Research Institute, to manage
the bookstore and provide readers with quick service.
</P>
<P>
It will be possible to rapidly ascertain sales values through
the network in order to supply large numbers of books promptly.
</P>
<P>
It will be possible to use the computer network to check the
orders and stockpiles of the books to ensure that the center will
display all new books published by all of the country's publishing
houses every year, Wang said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
