<HEADLINE> Tourists Dining With Monks On Chinese Mountain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Those who would like to know just
how it feels to sit down to a Buddhist-style meal with real monks
can now indulge that fancy for a different taste -- if they visit
Mount Wutai in north China's Shanxi Province, tourist authorities
say.
</P>
<P>
Hotel and restaurant businesses near the mountain, which is
sacred to Buddhists, have decided to start promoting tourism by
providing a variety of vegetarian dishes for tourists.
</P>
<P>
A range of 60 Buddhist dishes is now available for tourists who
can taste some delightful food and hear the story behind the dish.
</P>
<P>
Mount Wutai is one of the Buddhists' four major sacred
mountains in China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
