<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Denmark Increasing Investment in Tianjin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Construction of a
243-million-US-dollar Danish-funded pharmaceuticals project has
recently started in this north China port city.
</P>
<P>
The project, funded by Denmark's Novo Nordisk, a world-level
pharmaceuticals manufacturer, is the fourth and largest investment
item by a Danish company in Tianjin. The other three
Danish-funded enterprises in Tianjin have involved investments of
280,000 US dollars, 3.68 million US dollars, and 17 million US
dollars, respectively.
</P>
<P>
The project is also the second largest overseas-funded project
in the Tianjin Economic and Technological Development Zone after a
company funded by Motorola of the US.
</P>
<P>
The Danish-funded project will turn out a series of hi-tech
products like industrial enzymes, synthetic insulin, injectors,
and syringe needles.
</P>
<P>
It is the third enzymes production base of Novo Nordisk in the
world. The two others are in Denmark and the United States.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
