<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 13 Survive Plane Crash in Peru </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, May 6 (Xinhua) -- Thirteen people were found alive
Wednesday after a Boeing-737 carrying 87 persons crashed in a
northeastern jungle of Peru, military sources said.
</P>
<P>
The plane, flying from Lima to Andoas, capital of the
northeastern province of Loreto, crashed at 21:30 local time
Tuesday near the town of Tentayacu, only five kilometers away from
its destination.
</P>
<P>
Rescue workers found the 13 survivors some five hours after the
accident. A heavy rain there slowed down the rescue operation.
</P>
<P>
The plane belonged to Peru's Air Force and was leased by a
local oil company.
</P>
<P>
Of the 87 people aboard, the 79 passengers were employees of
the company and the rest were crew members.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the accident is under investigation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
