<HEADLINE> Inter-American Development Bank Announces Grant to Panama </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, May 6 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American Development
Bank (IADB) Wednesday announced a grant of 250 million U.S.
dollars to Panama in loans and donations earmarked for social
works.
</P>
<P>
The grant will be mainly channeled to the education sector for
projects including school rehabilitation and teacher training,
said Camalle Gaskin Reyes, IADB representative in Panama.
</P>
<P>
Another important part of the grant will be allocated to the
Public Works Ministry to improve streets and roads in the country.
</P>
<P>
The health sector will also receive some of the credits for the
refurbishing hospitals, purchasing medical equipment and personnel
training.
</P>
<P>
The IADB, based in Washington, has been increasing its grants
to Panama in the past few years, from 90 million U.S. dollars in
1996 to 143 million in 1997, Reyes said. 
</P>
