<HEADLINE> River Landslide Repairs Near Completion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, May 7 (Xinhua) -- The embankment of the Yangtze River
near Jiujiang City which caved in last week has been brought
under control, according to a report issued here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Since the cave-in occurred, the central and local
governments have raised 16.7 million yuan for the repairs,
said Cheng Xuanfa, director of the local water conservancy bureau.
</P>
<P>
In the four months ending last March, cave-ins were reported at
16 spots on the banks of the river, with a total length of 10.7 km.
</P>
<P>
In addition, 75 percent of the river banks near Jiujiang City
are below the state-set standards. Repairs will cost 60 million
yuan, Cheng said. 
</P>
