<HEADLINE> Soeharto to Attend G-15 Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian President Soeharto will
leave for Cairo on Saturday to attend the eighth summit meeting of
 Group 15 (G-15) from May 11 to 13, a senior official said.
</P>
<P>
The G-15 summit is expected to discuss the current world
situation, including the international money market and monetary
situation in developing countries, Foreign Minister Ali Alatas
said here last night.
</P>
<P>
Established in 1989, G-15 comprises Indonesia, Egypt, Malaysia,
Algeria, Argentina, Brazil, Chile, India, Jamaica, Mexico,
Nigeria, Peru, Senegal, Venezuela and Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
After attending the G-15 summit, Alatas said, Soeharto will pay
an official visit to Egypt from May 13 to 15 and hold talks with
his Egyptian counterpart, Hosni Mubarak, to strengthen relations
between the two countries, particularly in the economic field.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, the two sides will sign several agreements,
including one on the prevention of double taxation and a
memorandum of understanding between the two countries' central
banks, the official Antara News Agency reported Thursday.
</P>
</TEXT>
