<HEADLINE> Export Value of Thai Rice Increases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, May 7 (Xinhua) -- The value in baht of Thailand's rice
exports during the first four months this year soared by 243.5
percent to 33.6 billion baht, according to figures released by the
Foreign Trade Department of the Thai Commerce Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Compared with the first four months of last year, the dollar
value of the shipments rose by 26.7 percent to 750 million U.S.
dollars, based on the average exchange rate of 44.8 baht for the
dollar for the period.
</P>
<P>
Pracha Charutrakulchai, director-general of the department, was
quoted Thursday by The Bangkok Post as saying export prospects are
good for the rest of the year because of high demand in several
markets, notably Indonesia, the Philippines, Malaysia, Bangladesh
and Brazil.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia will need to import as much as 5 million tons of rice
to cope with shortages this year.
</P>
<P>
"Thai rice exports are expected to increase steadily to between
400,000 and 500,000 tons a month in line with heavy world market
demand, including from countries in Africa and the Middle East,"
Pracha said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
