<HEADLINE> Workshop on Women's Development Held in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, May 7 (Xinhua) -- A workshop on women's development is
being held here by the Myanmar National Committee for Women's
Affairs to draw up programs and plans for implementing the
country's women development projects.
</P>
<P>
The two-day workshop, which began on Wednesday, focuses on
various aspects of the projects including education, health and
socio-economic development, the official New Light of Myanmar
newspaper reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Lieutenant-General Khin Nyunt, first secretary of the Myanmar
State Peace and Development Council, said in his opening address
that significant characteristics of Myanmar women should be taken
into consideration when the workshop works out programs in line
with the tasks laid down by the Beijing Declaration adopted at the
U.N. Fourth World Conference on Women held in Beijing in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Khin Nyunt also emphasized that the programs should conform not
only to the political, economic and social objectives of the state
but also to Myanmar's cultural traditions and customs.
</P>
<P>
He said arrangements should be made to enable Myanmar women to
improve their abilities and qualities to contribute to
nation-building endeavors.
</P>
<P>
Papers will be presented at the workshop by officials and
professors of health and education departments and the Maternal
and Child Welfare Association on draft plans, women's education
and health and protection of Myanmar women against violence.
</P>
