<HEADLINE> AEK Athens Fined for Crowd Trouble </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, May 6 (Xinhua) -- Greek basketball team AEK Athens were
fined 100,000 marks (about 56,400 U.S. dollars) on Wednesday
following crowd trouble at their Final Four matches in Barcelona
in April.
</P>
<P>
AEK fans threw missiles and fought with police in their
semi-final victory over Benetton Treviso and again in the final
against Kinder Bologna, which the Italians won 58-44.
</P>
<P>
AEK were fined 50,000 marks (28,200 U.S. dollars) for each
incident and warned that a repeat of such trouble could lead to
disqualification from the next European competition for which they
qualify.
</P>
<P>
Kinder Bologna were fined 15,000 marks (8,460 U.S. dollars) as
a consequence of 400 of their fans entering the playing area after
the final, causing a 15-minute delay in the presentation
ceremony. 
</P>
</TEXT>
