<HEADLINE> Anhui Restructuring Export Mix </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, May 7 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui Province did 692
million US dollars-worth of foreign trade during the first quarter
of this year, a 2.9 percent rise compared to last year's same
period.
</P>
<P>
The amount included 413 million US dollars-worth of exports,
down 8.7 percent from the the same period of last year, due to the
influence of the ongoing Asian financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
In order to rein in the export slump, the province has been
restructuring its export mix by increasing exports to the EU, Russia,
Eastern Europe and Latin America, as well as by increasing its
exports of hi-tech and high-value-added products.
</P>
<P>
The province has 170 trading partners worldwide. One third of
its exports, most of which are primary products, are shipped to
Japan, the Republic of Korea and Southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
During the first quarter of this year, exports of machinery and
electronic products rose six percent over the same period of 1997.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
