<HEADLINE> London, Paris Stocks End Slightly up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 6 (Xinhua) -- Major stock markets in Europe ended
little changed Wednesday, with London and Paris slightly up while
Frankfurt moderately down.
</P>
<P>
Britain's FTSE-100 index of leading shares finished the session
5.9 points or 0.10 percent higher at 5,992.4, as a combination of
uncertainty over the direction of global interest rates and
concerns over the health of Asian economies plagued the market.
</P>
<P>
Some analysts believed sterling's recent pullback will give the
Bank of England leeway to push interest rates up at its latest
monetary policy meeting.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, hopes that news of merger talks between Daimler-Benz
and Chrysler would ignite a fresh rally on Wall Street came to
nothing.
</P>
